metadata.title: Piper J-3 Cub
aws::graph::propositions: L-4H was equipped with a controllable-pitch propeller.
UC-83A was a variant of the Piper J-3 Cub.
UC-83A consisted of two impressed J3L-65 aircraft.
UC-83A was later redesignated as L-4C.
TG-8 was a three-seat training glider variant of the Piper J-3 Cub.
XLNP-1 was the United States Navy designation for three experimental TG-8s.
NE-1 was the United States Navy designation for dual-control version of J3C-65.
NE-2 was similar to NE-1 with minor equipment changes.
B.S.3 was the Royal Thai Armed Forces designation for the L-4H and L-4J.
B.S.3 is written as บ.ส.๓ in Thai.
